From 03e445ef153ea0f316605aac2b588e40c7e52d9b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: krisztianfekete <git@krisztianfekete.org>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 20:32:34 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] dndcp: add a Wayland clipboard backend (wlr-data-control via
 wl-clipboard)

The dndcp plugin only ships an X11/GtkClipboard copy-paste backend
(copyPasteUIX11). Under a wlroots-based Wayland session (Sway, Hyprland,
river, ...) GtkClipboard uses the core wl_data_device protocol, which
requires keyboard focus and so cannot work for this windowless desktop
daemon. On guests where Xwayland is degraded (e.g. the VMware vmwgfx
driver, where dmabuf import fails) the X11 path cannot be used at all,
leaving host<->guest clipboard broken. See open-vm-tools issues #510 and
#792.

Add a Wayland platform implementation that reuses the existing GuestRPC
copy/paste protocol and the GuestCopyPasteMgr seam, and drives the local
clipboard with the wl-clipboard utilities (wl-copy / wl-paste). Those use
the wlr-data-control protocol, which works for an unfocused, windowless
client. The backend creates no Gtk::Main and never touches Xlib; it is
selected at runtime by CopyPasteDnDWrapper when WAYLAND_DISPLAY is set and
either there is no X DISPLAY or XDG_SESSION_TYPE=wayland, so a single build
serves both X11 and Wayland sessions.

Scope: plain UTF-8 text only (no images, RTF, or drag-and-drop). The MVP
shells out to wl-clipboard and therefore needs no new build dependencies
(no libwayland, no wayland-scanner).

New files:
  services/plugins/dndcp/copyPasteUIWayland.h
  services/plugins/dndcp/copyPasteUIWayland.cpp
  services/plugins/dndcp/dndGuestBase/copyPasteDnDWayland.h
  services/plugins/dndcp/copyPasteDnDWayland.cpp
